Suppose someone is operating a big server that handles lots of traffic.

 From time to time, you storm that server with spam.

NSA observes the corresponding traffic surges.

Statistical correlation between spam attacks and data flow eventually 
reveals the server.

We know silk road was attacked with spam and malware.  That it was 
attacked with spam, suggests that malware did not suffice.




